I genuinely think having a desktop computer is the factor most conductive to any intellectual development. Just the PC roaring and having the hardware keyboard, mouse connected to it inspires you to open 500 tabs and dwell among them. Never the same on laptop, it constricts you.

A smartphone's ethos is posting, laptops are ok for writing emails. But you need a PC to dig into old blogs, obscure forum networks, hypertext. The way it thrives off a desk, the spaciousness required, the individuality of its mechanical organs like processor, motherboard, etc.

Tablets/iPads are the worst, it's a slavery device. Impractical dimensions, made for pure consumption, informational pig trough. Only total freedom is in the PC. Solid, immovable bedroom axis, explicitly machine-like, opens possibility for deep research, quick software switching.
